openPOWERLINK is distributed under the BSD 2-Clause License; some
target/hardware-specific components are licensed under GPLv2. See the
openPOWERLINK source distribution (openPOWERLINK_V2) for the full license texts.

The bundled shared libraries (liboplkmn/oplkmn) are built from the openPOWERLINK
"complete MN" library using the userspace Ethernet driver (raw PF_PACKET sockets
on Linux; Npcap/WinPcap on Windows).

Npcap (Windows only)
--------------------
The Windows build links against the WinPcap-compatible Npcap SDK for compilation.
The Npcap runtime is NOT redistributed with this package; users must install it
separately from https://npcap.com under its own license.

This package's own code (the oplkwrap shim and the Python layer) is licensed
under the BSD 2-Clause License.
